properties.sfomuseum:description: Flight information packet produced by British Airways for Concorde service, comprising:a. light gray packet cover with flap, stamped imprinted “Concorde” with airline logo below on lower left corner, torn white square shape adhesive label closure with circular gray seal promoting the airline’s tenth anniversary for Concorde serviceb. brochure promoting Concorde service; white cover with airline servicemark; multipage bookletc. in-flight entertainment guide; gray cover with red “April” near top edge, black “Inflight Entertainment Guide” below, white area with full color musical notes; multipage bookletd. envelope containing schedule information, containing e and fe. timetable for flights between London and the United States, effective summer 1986; double-sided laminated cardf. timetable for flights between London and the United States, effective summer 1986; double-sided laminated cardg. poster with full color photographic image of in-flight British Airways Concordeh. blank flight certificate; single-sided sheeti. stationery envelope with embossed airline servicemarkj. stationery envelope with embossed airline servicemarkk. stationery sheet with embossed 10th anniversary seal at top and airline servicemark at bottoml. stationery sheet with embossed 10th anniversary seal at top and airline servicemark at bottomm. stationery sheet with embossed 10th anniversary seal at top and airline servicemark at bottomn. stationery sheet with embossed 10th anniversary seal at top and airline servicemark at bottomo. in-flight magazine, titled “Business life”, April / May 1986 issuep. in-flight magazine, titled “British Airways highlife”, April 1986 issue
